headline.main: FASCIST PUTS FAITH IN REICH PARTNER; Farinacci Says Nazis Will Not Betray Italy After the War Because Interests Coincide

lead_paragraph: ROME, Oct. 30 -- The Germans "will not betray" Italy after the war, Roberto Farinacci told 40,000 persons in Trieste in a speech he made to them on Tuesday, it was learned today when the Regime Fascista of Cremona arrived here. Italy's traditional enemy, he said, was not Germany but Habsburg Austria.
